                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 10: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee today discussed the issue of a higher public shareholding in listed companies with Sebi officials. In the Union Budget 2009-10, Mukherjee had proposed to raise the minimum stake of the public in listed firms to 25 per cent. The finance ministry is now working on a draft. Sebi chief C.B. Bhave was at the meeting with Mukherjee.                            
	 New Delhi, July 10: Tech Mahindra will complete the restatement of accounts of the acquired company Mahindra Satyam by the year-end, CEO Vineet Nayyar said. On whether global consultants Deloitte is being considered for statutory auditor, Nayyar said, Yes... Deloitte is under consideration.                   
	 Mumbai, July 10: Zenotech Laboratories said the schedule of open offer by Daiichi Sankyo for 20 per cent stake in the domestic entity would undergo a change.                                                                                                                            
